text.paragraph:
The pharmacokinetics of alfuzosin hydrochloride have not been studied in patients with mild hepatic impairment. Alfuzosin hydrochloride is contraindicated for use in patients with moderate or severe hepatic impairment [see Contraindications (
                           4
                           ), Warnings and Precautions (
                           5.3
                           ) and Clinical Pharmacology (
                           12.3
                           )].
